    "description": "Post-conflict constitutional moment coding for the CURRENT constitution of each country",
    "criterion": "The current constitution was adopted as a direct result of a negotiated peace process, post-war/post-genocide transition, or post-liberation state-building. Coups, authoritarian revisions, and routine amendments are excluded.",
    "unit": "Current constitution (not the country as an inherent property). A country may have both post-conflict and non-conflict constitutions in its history.",
    "coded_by": "Claude + Victor (preliminary — requires legal validation)",
